<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RUSSIA-CHECHNYA-REVIEW-2TAKES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A DEMOCRATIC WAR, PROPAGANDA AND ALL 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact the Los Angeles office
(Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
(bl) 
 By MICHAEL WINES   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOSCOW _ Oh, what a lovely war. Or so the Kremlin would like its
citizens to believe.
</P>
<P>
   From the outside, seven months of Chechen conflict seems a
bloodbath to rival any of the ethnic knifings that have scarred the
planet since the Cold War ended and nationalism slipped its leash.
