   FBN-FALCONS-FREEAGENTS _ For years, the Atlanta Falcons were not
active in the free agent market, deciding to stand pat with their
roster or adding only one or two players. This year, however, the
team was extremely active with the signing of Ashley Ambrose, Brady
Smith and Shawn Jefferson. In fact, the Falcons were so intent on
signing Ambrose that they flew him to Atlanta on the first day of
the free-agent signing period and used fellow cornerback Ray
Buchanan to help recruit him. A behind-the-scenes look at why the
Falcons were so active and some of the ways they were able to lure
players to Atlanta. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35.
MOVED
