   (NYT20) NEW YORK -- Feb. 26, 2000 -- NYPD-DIALLO-5 -- A woman is
distraught at a gathering Saturday morning outside the spot where
Amadou Diallo died a little more than a year ago, the vestibule of
his apartment building on Wheeler Avenue in the Bronx. The Diallo
family, dismayed by the Friday verdict acquitting four New York
City officers in the shooting death of Diallo, is expected to file
a multimillion-dollar lawsuit against the city. (Edward Keating/The
New York Times)
