 &QL; 
SAMMY (Phoenix) _ Salvatore Gravano never said he was a changed
man. Sure, the nation's most infamous mob turncoat had moved to
Arizona and started a construction business. Yes, he got along with
the neighbors, who sometimes stopped by with a cup of  &UR; coffee from
Starbucks. When a reporter found him living in Tempe, the
54-year-old who once admitted to 19 murders even grinned as he gave
an interview. By Dennis Wagner. Story will move in ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
